values:
Can you believe it's been exactly 3 YEARS since I've last updated?? A lot has changed, some better and some worse, and I wasn't going to post anything but since it's my anniversary with LJ I might as well lol.

I'm still with Sean and we have a beautiful daughter, Ariel, who is already 1 years old! She was born in May of '09 and she is my world. I currently do not have a job nor am I attending school like I should be, but it's tough right now and no one apparently wants to hire someone who's been out of a job for 2 years. As you might be able to tell I'm still in DE, no AZ for us lol.

That's really about it, my life isn't all that different except that most of my time is now spent with Holly and Jessica lol.

Maybe I'll make this a daily thing, maybe not, but until next time, au revoir. <3

So I might be moving to Arizona..

I'm tres excited.

Still have a lot to thing about though...

I'm finally home for break!!! My mood is ruined though because I have to go to a viewing tomorrow and a funeral on Monday. :( 

So I found out today that I got an A in my acting class and an A in my writing class (woot) but those are the only grades that I know of right now.

I am so fried from my finals that it's not even funny. I'm gonna go crash for the night...

Ok, it's been a majorly long time since I've put anything up here and I decided since I have nothing else to do that I would post on LJ.

We are now in finals week and my last day of class is tomorrow, so I basically have all week to study because my only 2 finals are on Friday and Saturday which is fine by me. I get to come home on Saturday and I stay home for a month! I'm so friggen excited because I get to see my kitties!!!

For those who don't know, I also got my tongue pierced back in September for my 18th birthday and I got a tattoo about a month ago of music and stuff. I think it's pretty sweet, personally. Anyways, it's on my back and this is what it looks like:

So other than that nothing is really new or exciting. I'm just hoping it doesn't snow up here until I get home so then I won't have to drive in that mess. Yup, so I'll try to get on here more often now because I can and try to keep everything up to date...

Wow, first update in what, a year? Something like that.

So I'm going to Cedar Crest College in Allentown, PA which is about 5 minutes from Dorney Park, so guess where I'm gonna be all year, lol. Luckily, Lindsay's going to college in Philly so we can see each other regularly and Holly will still be in DE so I can visit her when I come back home. The only person that I'll be away from and miss is Jess whom I rarely talk to anymore. *sigh* I'm just glad I'm done with all that high school shit and drama. Totally not worth it.

I can't wait til my 18th birthday!!! I'm totally gonna get stuff pierced and tattooed. It will be fun... I hope. Anyways, it's coming up soon and I'll be in college... I don't think I'm ready for it. I mean, I'm ready to be off on my own, but I don't want to start classes and stuff. Gah.

No one will probably read this, but that's ok since this is probably my last post... again. I'll see you guys again hopefully, but until then, adieu.

OMG guys, guess what! My mom bought tickets for next Saturday to see Chicago! How cool is that?! Lindsay was supposed to come with me, but she can't unless she finds someone to fill in for her at work... not unlikely, so that bites big time. So my mom is gonna go with me, which means I still get to go, but it's not the same. I'll still have some fun though. But I GET TO SEE CHICAGO!!!!!!! I don't even care if it's a broadway cast or not, but I have no idea where it is. I forget where it's at too... oops. I'm going to bed now, ciao!

Dear Santa...

Dear Santa,

This year I've been busy!

Last month I gave a wet willie, then I took it back (-5 points). In April I turned in for tearing the tag off a mattress (3 points). Last Sunday I pulled 's hair (-5 points). Last Monday I punched in the arm (-10 points). In May I helped hide a body (-173 points).

Overall, I've been naughty (-190 points). For Christmas I deserve a spanking!

Sincerely,
ilykeflamez

Write your letter to Santa! Enter your LJ username:

Omg, this has to be one of the cutest pictures I think I've ever seen. My mom thinks it's ugly, but I don't care what u guys think, I just love it!

Heehee, I'm watching Finding Nemo for the first time in like, a year. So I finally saw Charlie and the Chocolate Factory and it was awesome! I saw it two times and I'm not tired of it yet.

Omg guys, I saw SAW II yesterday and it was AMAZING. You should def. go see it, but u have to see the first one before you see the second. It IS required by me cuz I said so. Let's just say you won't get about half the movie if you don't.

So next week's Showstoppers and it's so weird cuz it feels like we haven't prepared nething for it at all when we have. I just don't wanna sit in Ms. Eldreth's room during the day cuz it gets soooo boring especially since I'm not in the first act at all. Grr, and Tori's gonna be there. SAVE ME! So does ne1 kno if we have a show Thursday or Friday during the day cuz I have no clue and my mom's friend wants to come see it during the day on Thurs. and I need to kno if we have a show.

So the past two days have been wonderful cuz naturally my mom had to work yesterday and my dad was gone for some reason and Nick went to Joe's house, so I was alone! Of course by the time I got back from the movies, my dad was home, but that's ok. Today I was alone until about 2:30 cuz my parents went furniture shopping cuz we're getting a new living room. Whoop whoop.

So that's about it, and I guess I'm done. See u guys on Monday. Ciao!

Woot woot! Today's my b-day! I'm finally 17! Last night I got the CUTEST purse, but you'll have to wait til school to find out what it is...  and I got the Josh Gracin CD last night, the Nightmare before Christmas soundtrack, and the Phantom of the Opera DVD.

I can't really say this is the "best birthday ever" when in actuality it's not really that great. I was supposed to hang out with Jessica today, but I called her and she wasn't home. I left a message, but she never called me back. I even saw her at the mall last night and she said she still wanted to do something. Another thing, my dad hasn't even told me happy birthday. Wtf is up with that?! I don't like him that much, but he could at least say "happy birthday" once or something.

So I'm watchin Hook right now and I love this movie just for the dinner scene where Peter starts imagining again. I just mainly want the desserts but... o well.

Omg, I love Stephanie's present! She got me a necklace that has 2 pics of Rupert Grint in it, a bracelet w/ 5 pic of Rupert Grint, and a Harry Potter candle. Lindz got me a really cute blue and black sweater thing and a pretty blue necklace that matches almost perfectly.

Right now I really wanna go to Party City and get one of those outfits that Lindz, Steph and I were lookin at. Urgh, I have enough money for one but I don't feel like going right now. Maybe I'll go after school w/ Lindz and I'll get one or something.

K, well I've bored u people enough, and I'm done. In about an hour I get to go eat chinese food! And it's supposedly even bigger than the one in Bear that we already go to. MORE CHINESE FOOD!!!! Haha, I'm such a fatty... k bye!

GUYS THIS IS REALLY IMPORTANT. IF ANYONE HAS A KARAOKE MACHINE THAT THEY WILL LET ME BORROW, PLEASE LET ME KNOW!!! I NEED IT BY THURSDAY OCT. 6 SO I CAN USE IT ON OCT. 7. I WILL PICK IT UP AND DROP IT OFF SO YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO ANYTHING. THANKS GUYS!

Bio trip next week! Woot woot! I'm so excited! I just hope Lindsay can go cuz she's the only one of my friends that signed up to go besides Stephanie... yea. So newayz, 7 days til my birthday!!! I'm actually not really that excited cuz nothing changes, but I can see Rated-R movies now, lol, I kno, I'm a youngun. 

Does ne1 kno if we have nething due for AP Lit. on Thursday or Friday? Mmk, update over.

OMG GUYS!!!!! GILLIGAN DIED!!!!!!! Ack!!!! This is so upsetting! I LOVED that show.  Ah, what r u gonna do? SUE!!! LoL, j/k guys.

So classes are lookin better than they were... still hate english but other than that... I think I'm gonna fail AP Bio cuz I'm just not gettin it. I mean, I know it until someone asks me a question about it then I'm like, "uhhhh". 

Well I have anatomy notes to do... ciao!

P.S. Guys, 19 UNTIL MY 17TH BIRTHDAY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! AND I WAS BORN ON A FULL MOON!

School started on Tuesday... Let's just say it wasn't TOO bad. The first day was actually really good cuz I didn't have English. I HATE that class! I would switch to the other AP class cuz it has less people, but I can't change my schedule. Whatever, I'll just wing it.

So yea, nuthin really new this year, 'cept a couple new people who I don't know, but it feels like we never left at all. OMG, I'm actually in the right vocal class this year! AND... Karl's in my class!!!!! YAY!!!!!!!

K, I guess that's it. Watchin' Dirty Dancin which is one of the BEST MOVIES EVER!!!! Hahaha, oh, I need to ask u guys something. I need to get music for the party that's coming up and I need to know if you guys have any of the songs. Well here's the list. Some of it may be corny, but it has a reason for being there:


     1.) Don't Cha - The Pussycat Dolls
     2.) Listen to your Heart - D.H.T
     3.) Brass Bed (Stay With Me) - Josh Gracin
     4.) Pon De Replay



Actually, that's all I remember right now... crap. But if I think of more, I'll ask. PLZ, if u have ne of the songs, can I borrow the CD so that I can copy it? Thanks a billion guys! Mwah!

Geez guys, how long has it been now??? whoo, right now I'm "reading" my AP books. Actually, I'm listening to them on tape so it'll be over faster. Fun fun! School in 3 days! I am soooo not ready to go back... I have to do most of my English, and still half of my biology, so don't call me on monday cuz I'm gonna be doin homework aaalllllll day.


So newayz, I have good news! I don't know how many of you have heard, but Jess had her heart transplant and so far she's doing well. I haven't heard nething in a week but as long as I don't hear nething, than I kno nothing bad happened.

More good news! Chester's coming to my b-day party!!!!!!!!!!!!! I'm so excited, and he's gonna be my "date"! Whoo! Sometimes I really love Tori. Oooh, and he's single now! Yup yup, his gf broke up with him a couple weeks ago. I know this sounds mean, but I'm sooo happy about that. Not that I think I have a chance, but ya never know!

Ooooh, last good news! Lindsay's almost done my dress! All she has to do now is make my train and then it's done!!!!! hahahahahahahaha, I can't wail til the party!



K, now I'm done and I'm gonna pay attention to my book now, bye!

I just can't believe this happened... 

Holly called me last night and told my dad what happened and he called me on my cell phone. I didn't believe him when he told me because he's old and often doesn't hear things the right way. So I was still crying anyways and trying not to crash the car and I decided that I needed to confirm this horrid event. I drove over to where it happened and I saw all the signs for Matt saying "We miss you Daggett!" and my heart just sank. He died not even 2 minutes away from where I live so now everytime I go past it, I'm going to think of him and just start crying. It's not fair! He was taken too soon and he was the nicest guy I've ever met. 

He was my first(and only) date to a school dance and I think I'm never going to have one so he'll always have that place. The last time I hung out with him was at the ice skating rink a couple of weeks ago. Holly was trying to teach me how to skate and he was holding my other hand. I kept yelling at him not to let go, don't let go!... and he never did. There was a point in when I grabbed the wall and he went off with his friends, but he never let go...

Rest in Peace Matt, we love you and will always miss you.
Matt Daggett
May 5, 1988 - March 19, 2005
